OK, I made that up, but think it’s within range of the actual number. With more than 3,200 breweries operating across the country and more than double that number interested in exporting here (and with each releasing on average 14 beers during the year), then maybe that number makes sense. Today’s national beer community is the celebration of literally thousands of smaller ones. Creativity, art, innovation and acumen come together on what seems like every corner to renew a long-forgotten brewing method or refine a pursuit of style.

Brewer of the Lucky Pint Brewery. Widely known for his exquisite personal style, his lectures on the history of beer and the art of brewing. 
Author of the numerous articles on brewing and a many time winner of the biggest brewing contests.

Phone: +1(800)123-4566

<h2>About the Course</h2>
Introduces concepts and skills to plan and conduct evaluations of social programs. Over the semester students will work with a client to produce an evaluation plan.

Students will learn about negotiating a plan with a client, working with stakeholders, forms of evaluation (impact evaluation, consumer satisfaction, MSC, qualitative designs), evaluation ethics, how to develop indicators and program logic, and finally how to ensure evaluation findings are disseminated and utilised.

[trx_title type="4" style="regular"]OUR BREWERY'S STORY[/trx_title]
[vc_column_text]
The Lucky Pint has gone through a serious evolution starting as a tiny home brewery
and ended up being a big chain of pubs.  

Over all these long years we have been accumulating only the best brewing traditions and recipes. We keep surprising our customers and ourselves. Wanna get the best brewing experience? You’re in the right place!  <br/>
[/vc_column_text]

The Lucky Pint has gone through a serious evolution starting as a tiny home brewery and ended up being a big chain of pubs. Wanna get the best brewing experience? You're in the right place!

Over all these long years we have been accumulating only the best brewing traditions and recipes. We keep surprising our customers and ourselves. Turns out - nothing tastes as good as our beer!

green and join us as we celebrate St. Patricks Day with tons of beer and good cheer.

The Lucky Pint has gone through a serious evolution starting as a tiny home brewery and ended up being a big chain of pubs. Wanna get the best brewing experience? You’re in the right place!

Over all these long years we have been accumulating only the best brewing traditions and recipes. We keep surprising our customers and ourselves. Turns out – nothing tastes as good as our beer!

[trx_section bg_tint="" dedicated="no" pan="no" align="center" scroll="no" bg_overlay="0" top="90" bg_texture="0" class="block_bg"]
[trx_content  bottom="80"]
[trx_title type="1" h1_styling="1" style="regular" align="center" animation="fadeInUp" bottom="35"]Join Us For A Beer![/trx_title]
[trx_block dedicated="no" align="center" pan="no" scroll="no" color="#9b8c85" bg_overlay="0" bg_texture="0" font_size="16" bottom="70"]
[vc_column_text]
At our pub, we proudly offer our guests to taste our best types of beer brewed from carefully selected<br/> barley, wheat and hops. Take a look below to learn more about our best beers.
[/vc_column_text]
[/trx_block]
[trx_columns fluid="no" animation="fadeInUp" count="4"]
	[trx_column_item align="center"]
[trx_image url="http://tavern.axiomthemes.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/beer-1.png" shape="square" animation="fadeInUp"]
[trx_title type="5" style="regular" align="center" color="#b55126" top="30"]PILSNER[/trx_title]
[vc_column_text]It's a clean and simple pale lager and one of the more popular beer varieties. [/vc_column_text]
[/trx_column_item]
	[trx_column_item align="center"]
[trx_image url="http://tavern.axiomthemes.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/beer-2.png" shape="square" animation="fadeInUp"]
[trx_title type="5" style="regular" align="center" color="#b55126" top="30"]STOUTS[/trx_title]
[vc_column_text]Stouts have an unclear history, yet it's strongly held by many that they derive from porters. [/vc_column_text]
[/trx_column_item]
	[trx_column_item align="center"]
[trx_image url="http://tavern.axiomthemes.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/beer-3.png" shape="square" animation="fadeInUp"]
[trx_title type="5" style="regular" align="center" color="#b55126" top="30"]PALE ALE[/trx_title]
[vc_column_text]Pale ale is one of the world's most popular beer styles. It's made with the use of pale malt. [/vc_column_text]
[/trx_column_item]
	[trx_column_item align="center"]
[trx_image url="http://tavern.axiomthemes.loc/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/beer-4.png" shape="square" animation="fadeInUp"]
[trx_title type="5" style="regular" align="center" color="#b55126" top="30"]BROWN ALE[/trx_title]
[vc_column_text]It's a very old style beer, whose history dates back to unhopped ales. [/vc_column_text]
[/trx_column_item]
[/trx_columns]
[/trx_content]
[/trx_section]
[/trx_gap]

Brewer of the Lucky Pint Brewery. Widely known for his exquisite personal style, his lectures on the history of beer and the art of brewing. 
Author of the numerous articles on brewing and a many time winner of the biggest brewing contests. 

Email John: <a href="mailto:info@yoursitename.com">info@yoursitename.com</a>
Phone: +1(800)123-4566

15:35:34";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2016-01-27 15:35:34";s:12:"post_content";s:4696:"[vc_row][vc_column][trx_section bottom="4em"][trx_title h1_styling="1" align="center" color="#000000"]Our Support Policy[/trx_title][trx_columns top="small" margins=""][trx_column_item][vc_column_text]
<ul>
	<li>To get a pre-purchase advice, you may post in the theme’s forum.</li>
	<li>To get a response more promptly, you are recommended to use our Ticket-system.</li>
	<li>We try to answer your questions within 1-10 hours. However, if any delay occurs, it doesn’t mean that we forgot about you. Some of the issues require testing and analyzing, so we can resolve it effectively.</li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][/trx_column_item][trx_column_item][vc_column_text]
<ul>
	<li>Please note! We do not provide support, if you do not have the purchase code.</li>
	<li>Item support does not include:
<ol>
	<li>Customization and installation.</li>
	<li>Support for third party software and plugins.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][/trx_column_item][/trx_columns][/trx_section][trx_line color="#ded9cd"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" scheme="light"][vc_column][trx_section top="large" bottom="large"][trx_title h1_styling="1" align="center" color="#000000" bottom="tiny"]How to use our Support System[/trx_title][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1453908740529{margin-top: 25px !important;margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<p style="text-align: center;">Axiom technical support is always there to assist their users with all the technical questions regarding Axiom products.</p>

[/vc_column_text][trx_columns top="tiny" margins=""][trx_column_item][trx_image url="2037"][/trx_column_item][trx_column_item][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1453908465594{margin-top: 20px !important;}"]
<ol>
	<li>In the ‘Item Details’ there is a clickable banner “Support Sys”, which leads you to tickets.</li>
	<li>Or you may simply follow this link: <a href="http://axiom.ticksy.com">axiom.ticksy.com</a>.</li>
	<li>Enter your purchase key and register in the system.</li>
	<li>To avoid a confusion, please use your own ThemeForest login in Support System.</li>
	<li>Fill out the ticket form.</li>
</ol>
[/vc_column_text][/trx_column_item][/trx_columns][/trx_section][trx_line color="#ded9cd"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row"][vc_column][trx_section top="large" bottom="large"][trx_title h1_styling="1" align="center"]How to find a purchase key[/trx_title][trx_columns top="small" margins=""][trx_column_item][trx_image url="2009" top="tiny"][/trx_column_item][trx_column_item][vc_column_text]
<ul>
	<li>Open the "downloads" tab in your account.</li>
	<li>Find our theme in the list of products.</li>
	<li>Click "download" button, and in the drop-down menu select "license certificate &amp; purchase code".</li>
</ul>
[/vc_column_text][/trx_column_item][/trx_columns][/trx_section][trx_line color="#ded9cd"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" scheme="light"][vc_column][trx_section top="large" bottom="large"][trx_title h1_styling="1" align="center" bottom="tiny"]Hosting[/trx_title][trx_title type="4" align="center" top="small" bottom="small"]Recommended hostings:[/trx_title][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1453908752773{margin-top: 30px !important;}"]
<p style="text-align: center;">Axiom offers only the best products and services and recommends them to their customers. One of the most important services is HOSTING. Unlike any cheap hostings that usually have limited resources which causes many problems to the site owners, quality hosting gives a client a fair amount of resources sufficient for any website and any task. By using quality hosting you can rest assured that your site will work smoothly. If you happen to use such hosting with limited resources (e.g. GoDaddy!), you may experience issues with “one-click install” feature. In that case, you are always welcome to contact our support team to get qualified help.</p>

[/vc_column_text][trx_columns margins=""][trx_column_item align="center"][trx_image url="2010" link="https://secure1.inmotionhosting.com/cgi-bin/gby/clickthru.cgi?id=themerex"][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://secure1.inmotionhosting.com/cgi-bin/gby/clickthru.cgi?id=themerex" target="_blank">http://www.inmotionhosting.com</a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Get more than <strong>30% discount</strong> on a hosting plan.</p>

[/vc_column_text][/trx_column_item][trx_column_item align="center"][trx_image url="2011" link="https://mediatemple.net/"][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://mediatemple.net/" target="_blank">http://mediatemple.net</a></p>
